    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a house purchase, is essentially a secure holding place for funds and documents until all the conditions of the sale are met. Think of it like a temporary, neutral holding area, managed by a third party, usually a title company or an escrow agent. It's vital because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money and the deed transfer only happen when everything is squared away. Without it, you'd be handing over your hard-earned cash to a seller who might suddenly decide to go back on their word, which is a risk no one wants!",
